9
00:00:47.782 --> 00:00:50.985
The latest report came from
deep inside the Sognefjord.

10
00:00:51.151 --> 00:00:52.720
What exactly did you see there?

11
00:00:53.287 --> 00:00:56.256
Yes. I. uh-- I. uh. saw a shadow

12
00:00:56.390 --> 00:00:59.126
that seemed to. uh.
be breaking the surface.

13
00:01:00.394 --> 00:01:02.764
[music continues]

14
00:01:04.431 --> 00:01:06.066
[interviewer] So you took
your binoculars and went

15
00:01:06.199 --> 00:01:08.703
-towards the window?
-Yes. I did and
when I looked out.

16
00:01:08.836 --> 00:01:12.707
the window. I saw what
looked like a wave in the sea.

17
00:01:18.178 --> 00:01:19.881
But I wasn't sure...

18
00:01:20.180 --> 00:01:21.448
about the shape of the thing.

19
00:01:21.583 --> 00:01:24.318
I really wasn't able
to make out what it was.

20
00:01:26.219 --> 00:01:29.089
[interviewer] Uh. could you tell
me roughly how big it was?

21
00:01:29.222 --> 00:01:32.760
No. I don't wanna answer that.
because I'm not exactly sure.

22
00:01:33.027 --> 00:01:34.494
But it was at least 200 meters.

23
00:01:34.629 --> 00:01:37.331
give or take a few.
I'm sure of that.

24
00:01:37.865 --> 00:01:39.499
[somber music continues]

25
00:01:44.906 --> 00:01:47.675
[interviewer] <i>Navy vessels.</i>
<i>helicopters and planes</i>

26
00:01:47.809 --> 00:01:50.177
<i>all searched the area for</i>
<i>several days.</i>

27
00:01:50.377 --> 00:01:53.581
<i>Was there an unidentified</i>
<i>submarine in the Sognefjord.</i>

28
00:01:53.715 --> 00:01:54.882
<i>or wasn't there?</i>

29
00:01:55.049 --> 00:01:56.551
[helicopter rumbling]

30
00:01:56.751 --> 00:01:59.219
<i>But it will probably be years</i>
<i>before that question</i>

31
00:01:59.353 --> 00:02:01.022
<i>and many others are answered.</i>

32
00:02:01.154 --> 00:02:04.525
<i>Maybe they will remain</i>
<i>unanswered forever.</i>

33
00:02:08.029 --> 00:02:09.864
[music increases. then halts]

34
00:02:13.034 --> 00:02:14.669
[narrator] <i>The Sognefjord.</i>

35
00:02:16.004 --> 00:02:17.772
[engine rumbling]

36
00:02:24.912 --> 00:02:27.582
[muffled rumbling]

37
00:02:30.685 --> 00:02:32.219
[engine rumbles]

38
00:02:33.054 --> 00:02:34.756
[man whooping]

39
00:02:38.826 --> 00:02:40.828
[men grunting]

40
00:02:44.398 --> 00:02:46.366
[man howling]

41
00:02:49.871 --> 00:02:51.706
[howls. then echoes]

42
00:02:51.839 --> 00:02:54.408
-[howls. then echoes]
-[chuckles]

43
00:02:54.809 --> 00:02:56.844
[echo continues]

44
00:02:57.145 --> 00:02:59.212
[seagulls squawking]

45
00:02:59.881 --> 00:03:01.616
[somber music]

46
00:03:01.983 --> 00:03:03.718
[engine rumbling]

47
00:03:10.190 --> 00:03:12.660
[music turns eerie]

48
00:03:32.113 --> 00:03:34.347
-Hold on! Hold on!
-[grunts]

49
00:03:39.486 --> 00:03:40.955
[music continues]

50
00:03:43.958 --> 00:03:46.259
-Careful! Oh. shit!
-[screams]

51
00:03:47.562 --> 00:03:49.697
[muffled grunting]

52
00:03:53.134 --> 00:03:54.602
[screaming]

53
00:04:06.480 --> 00:04:07.949
[narrator reads]

54
00:04:13.253 --> 00:04:14.956
[soft suspenseful music]

55
00:04:20.528 --> 00:04:22.697
[indistinct underwater ambiance]

56
00:04:26.100 --> 00:04:27.935
[soft whirring]

57
00:04:55.630 --> 00:04:57.532
[music increases then halts]

58
00:04:57.965 --> 00:04:59.801
[heavy breathing]

59
00:05:02.236 --> 00:05:03.470
[sighs]

60
00:05:04.005 --> 00:05:05.840
[cellphone buzzing]

61
00:05:14.414 --> 00:05:15.917
[computer beeping]

62
00:05:17.185 --> 00:05:19.854
[narrator]
<i>Institute of Marine Research.</i>

63
00:05:22.023 --> 00:05:24.559
[underwater growling]

64
00:05:27.094 --> 00:05:28.796
[indistinct whirring]

65
00:05:29.030 --> 00:05:30.463
[cellphone buzzing]

66
00:05:34.268 --> 00:05:36.070
-[woman] Hey. there!
-[Larsen] <i>Hey. listen.</i>

67
00:05:36.204 --> 00:05:37.772
<i>I know it's your day off. but</i>
<i>did you happen to see</i>

68
00:05:37.905 --> 00:05:40.107
<i>-the email I sent you?</i>
-Oh. I'm sorry. uh--

69
00:05:40.241 --> 00:05:41.441
I-- I haven't had time.

70
00:05:41.576 --> 00:05:43.578
And. um. now
the movement pattern

71
00:05:43.711 --> 00:05:45.445
has changed.
so I have to go back out.

72
00:05:45.580 --> 00:05:47.315
I have to move
that hydrophone before that.

73
00:05:47.447 --> 00:05:49.784
<i>Right. right. well.</i>
<i>I need you on an inspection.</i>

74
00:05:49.917 --> 00:05:51.519
What do you mean. an inspection?

75
00:05:51.819 --> 00:05:54.655
<i>We got an alert about a</i>
<i>fish farm on the west coast.</i>

76
00:05:56.123 --> 00:05:58.092
So call the
Food Safety Authority.

77
00:05:58.358 --> 00:06:01.896
<i>Uh... no. uh. this is</i>
<i>a bit more specialized.</i>

78
00:06:02.462 --> 00:06:04.632
-[woman] Okay.
<i>-And it's more exciting</i>
<i>than counting</i>

79
00:06:04.765 --> 00:06:07.735
<i>porpoises and tallying</i>
<i>walruses and also</i>
<i>a fjord. to be honest.</i>

80
00:06:08.069 --> 00:06:10.738
Well. what can I tell you?
They were here first.

81
00:06:11.205 --> 00:06:13.808
<i>Nobody knows more</i>
<i>about this than you. Johanne.</i>

82
00:06:14.474 --> 00:06:15.910
<i>This is your field.</i>

83
00:06:16.110 --> 00:06:17.144
[chuckles]

84
00:06:17.345 --> 00:06:18.913
Where on the west coast?

85
00:06:19.547 --> 00:06:20.748
<i>Vangsnes.</i>

86
00:06:21.048 --> 00:06:22.149
[suspenseful music]

87
00:06:23.551 --> 00:06:26.354
But you know Vangsnes
is a no-go for me.

88
00:06:26.654 --> 00:06:28.356
We've talked about this.
[stutters]

89
00:06:28.488 --> 00:06:29.957
You know
I can't go there. Kjell.

90
00:06:30.091 --> 00:06:32.293
<i>They're doing sonic</i>
<i>delousing. It's your invention.</i>

91
00:06:32.425 --> 00:06:34.862
Either way. you know
I'm done with that industry.

92
00:06:35.196 --> 00:06:37.832
<i>Yeah. well. I'll send you</i>
<i>a video from</i>
<i>the whistleblower now.</i>

93
00:06:37.965 --> 00:06:40.968
Okay. I have to get going now.
I have a birthday thing.

94
00:06:41.102 --> 00:06:43.070
<i>Fine. but just get up there</i>
<i>and send me reports</i>

95
00:06:43.204 --> 00:06:44.471
<i>as you go along. please.</i>

96
00:06:44.839 --> 00:06:47.241
God. now they're singing
Happy Birthday and everything.

97
00:06:47.375 --> 00:06:48.943
So we'll talk later. okay?

98
00:06:49.476 --> 00:06:51.112
[melancholic music]

99
00:07:10.197 --> 00:07:11.431
[loud thud]

100
00:07:12.566 --> 00:07:14.434
[vehicle beeping]

101
00:07:22.944 --> 00:07:25.379
-[music fades]
-[seat whirrs]

102
00:07:25.846 --> 00:07:27.148
[notification chimes]

103
00:07:32.920 --> 00:07:34.454
-[man on video] <i>Holy shit!</i>
-[mysterious music]

104
00:07:34.588 --> 00:07:35.756
<i>Uh. there must be</i>
<i>hundreds of them.</i>

105
00:07:35.890 --> 00:07:37.959
<i>Look! Look. Maria! It's crazy!</i>

106
00:07:38.626 --> 00:07:40.294
[Maria on video]
<i>They're going crazy!</i>

107
00:07:40.795 --> 00:07:42.196
[man] <i>I know! What's going on?</i>

108
00:07:42.330 --> 00:07:43.965
[Maria] <i>There's loads</i>
<i>over here. Tommy!</i>

109
00:07:44.765 --> 00:07:47.201
<i>It must be the fish farm.</i>
<i>I bet it is.</i>

110
00:07:48.736 --> 00:07:50.037
[Tommy] <i>Yeah!</i>

111
00:07:50.171 --> 00:07:52.239
[sighs]
<i>This is bad. I mean seriously.</i>

112
00:07:52.373 --> 00:07:53.874
[Tommy] <i>All those fuckers!</i>

113
00:07:58.512 --> 00:07:59.947
[music continues]

114
00:08:06.954 --> 00:08:08.923
[music turns suspenseful]

115
00:08:11.525 --> 00:08:13.027
[cellphone line beeping]

116
00:08:13.694 --> 00:08:17.064
[female voice] <i>The person</i>
<i>you are calling cannot be</i>
<i>reached at this moment.</i>

117
00:08:19.800 --> 00:08:21.669
[plane rumbling]

118
00:08:21.836 --> 00:08:23.270
[music fades]

119
00:08:25.172 --> 00:08:30.111
This 9000-year-old
arrowhead proves it.

120
00:08:30.344 --> 00:08:32.013
[woman speaking Japanese]

121
00:08:32.179 --> 00:08:35.149
The glaciers. they're melting at
a great pace.

122
00:08:35.783 --> 00:08:38.786
But... there is an upside.

123
00:08:39.653 --> 00:08:40.955
The water from the glacier.

124
00:08:41.088 --> 00:08:43.357
the crisp. clear. pure water

125
00:08:43.491 --> 00:08:45.126
mixes with the fjord.

126
00:08:45.326 --> 00:08:46.827
[woman translating]

127
00:08:47.128 --> 00:08:50.831
It's the deepest fjord
in the world. 1300 meters.

128
00:08:51.232 --> 00:08:52.733
[woman translating]

129
00:08:53.167 --> 00:08:56.871
And it's the perfect place for
our superior salmon to grow up.

130
00:08:57.304 --> 00:08:59.106
[man speaking Japanese]

131
00:09:02.243 --> 00:09:03.544
[woman] Oh!

132
00:09:03.711 --> 00:09:05.813
Take a low pass
over the fish farm.

133
00:09:06.447 --> 00:09:07.715
[engine rumbling]

134
00:09:11.185 --> 00:09:12.486
[hopeful music]

135
00:09:12.820 --> 00:09:14.121
Hey. look up.

136
00:09:18.092 --> 00:09:19.126
Woo!

137
00:09:26.867 --> 00:09:30.571
So. this is where the magic
happens.

138
00:09:31.872 --> 00:09:34.241
We use this room
to adjust and monitor

139
00:09:34.375 --> 00:09:36.210
our Sonic Lice technology.

140
00:09:37.546 --> 00:09:38.646
[man] The arrowhead worked?

141
00:09:38.779 --> 00:09:40.347
To ensure...

142
00:09:41.248 --> 00:09:45.252
...the quality
and the health of our salmon.

143
00:09:45.386 --> 00:09:48.589
Georg here
is our head technician.

144
00:09:50.357 --> 00:09:53.094
[speaking Japanese]

145
00:09:55.362 --> 00:09:56.565
[chuckles]

146
00:09:56.797 --> 00:09:58.833
-Uh. video.
-[Georg] Yeah. [clears throat]

147
00:09:58.966 --> 00:10:00.968
If I can direct
your attention this way.

148
00:10:01.102 --> 00:10:02.403
[male voice on video]
<i>Welcome to Vangsnes.</i>

149
00:10:02.537 --> 00:10:05.039
<i>A place where innovation</i>
<i>meets nature.</i>

150
00:10:05.507 --> 00:10:07.808
<i>The salmon in the fjord</i>
<i>is under attack</i>

151
00:10:07.942 --> 00:10:09.977
<i>by lice that works</i>
<i>much like a parasite</i>

152
00:10:10.311 --> 00:10:13.347
<i>that attaches itself</i>
<i>to a host and kills it.</i>

153
00:10:13.582 --> 00:10:15.382
<i>Sonic Lice is the solution.</i>

154
00:10:15.517 --> 00:10:17.685
<i>Using</i>
<i>state-of-the-art technology</i>

155
00:10:17.818 --> 00:10:19.253
<i>to safely remove the lice.</i>

156
00:10:19.386 --> 00:10:21.856
<i>our new transducers</i>
<i>are using soundwaves</i>

157
00:10:21.989 --> 00:10:23.558
<i>to remove the parasite.</i>

158
00:10:24.125 --> 00:10:26.460
<i>This is a safe</i>
<i>and environmentally friendly</i>

159
00:10:26.595 --> 00:10:27.895
<i>way to save the salmon.</i>

160
00:10:28.229 --> 00:10:30.097
<i>Join us at Western Salmon.</i>

161
00:10:30.297 --> 00:10:34.168
<i>where tomorrow's technology</i>
<i>creates a better everyday life.</i>

162
00:10:34.503 --> 00:10:36.704
<i>Sonic Lice to the rescue.</i>

163
00:10:37.104 --> 00:10:40.141
<i>Sonic Lice.</i>
<i>the future of salmon.</i>

164
00:10:40.274 --> 00:10:43.277
-[man speaking Japanese]
-[woman chuckles]

165
00:10:44.712 --> 00:10:45.779
Thank you. Georg.

166
00:10:46.548 --> 00:10:49.483
That was. of course. uh.
an educational video.

167
00:10:50.017 --> 00:10:51.952
[muffled hip-hop music]

168
00:10:52.853 --> 00:10:55.122
[music continues on speakers]

169
00:10:55.923 --> 00:10:57.291
[music stops]

170
00:11:06.467 --> 00:11:07.735
[Johanne sighs]

171
00:11:11.038 --> 00:11:12.673
[cellphone line ringing]

172
00:11:13.374 --> 00:11:14.842
[Erik]
<i>Hey. you've reached Erik.</i>

173
00:11:14.975 --> 00:11:16.810
<i>Leave a message</i>
<i>after the beep.</i>

174
00:11:20.080 --> 00:11:22.416
There's the brain behind
Sonic Lice himself.

175
00:11:22.716 --> 00:11:27.421
Erik is our head aquatic
engineer and my on-site manager.

176
00:11:28.289 --> 00:11:30.057
Sonic Lice is impressive.
but I heard

177
00:11:30.191 --> 00:11:32.426
the sonic sound treatment
can stress the salmon

178
00:11:32.561 --> 00:11:34.094
and stop their growth.

179
00:11:34.828 --> 00:11:35.996
No. not at all. no.

180
00:11:36.130 --> 00:11:37.532
We take great pride
in the well-being

181
00:11:37.666 --> 00:11:39.833
-and the health of our fish.
-[woman translating]

182
00:11:39.967 --> 00:11:41.702
The trick is finding
the right frequency.

183
00:11:42.136 --> 00:11:43.572
Too low. it doesn't work.

184
00:11:43.704 --> 00:11:45.272
Too high. yeah. it can.

185
00:11:45.406 --> 00:11:47.808
And it can even disrupt the
entire ecosystem in the fjord.

186
00:11:47.942 --> 00:11:49.810
[speaking Japanese]

187
00:11:50.077 --> 00:11:53.047
What do you mean
by disrupt the ecosystem?

188
00:11:53.180 --> 00:11:55.049
There's no chance of that.
[chuckles]

189
00:11:55.783 --> 00:11:57.586
We have developed the software.

190
00:11:57.718 --> 00:12:01.388
Adjusting the frequency based on
the stress levels of our fish.

191
00:12:01.556 --> 00:12:04.024
But the transducer
is the heart of Sonic Lice.

192
00:12:04.158 --> 00:12:06.794
-[speaking Japanese]
-[woman] Elegant stuff.

193
00:12:07.494 --> 00:12:08.862
Cake?

194
00:12:10.097 --> 00:12:12.366
Shiro. you wanna start?

195
00:12:13.334 --> 00:12:14.468
[narrator reads]

196
00:12:14.902 --> 00:12:16.504
[upbeat music]

197
00:12:16.638 --> 00:12:18.839
[man on microphone]
<i>Up next is Jonnes!</i>

198
00:12:19.139 --> 00:12:21.543
<i>He's a regular</i>
<i>here in Vangsnes.</i>

199
00:12:21.676 --> 00:12:23.110
[people cheering]

200
00:12:23.377 --> 00:12:25.479
<i>Jonnes. are you ready to jump?</i>

201
00:12:26.447 --> 00:12:28.983
[woman] Johanne! Johanne!

202
00:12:32.052 --> 00:12:33.153
-Hi!
-[Johanne chuckles] Hi!

203
00:12:33.688 --> 00:12:36.991
-It's been a long time.
-[woman] Very long. [chuckles]

204
00:12:39.193 --> 00:12:41.862
-Hey. Henriette. can I be rude?
-Oh. hey Biruth. oh. yes.

205
00:12:41.996 --> 00:12:43.364
Uh. just one second.

206
00:12:44.064 --> 00:12:45.734
-What happened?
-[indistinct]

207
00:12:46.166 --> 00:12:49.103
[men laughing
and cheering indistinctly]

208
00:12:51.438 --> 00:12:52.973
[man on microphone]
<i>Full-speed dive!</i>

209
00:12:53.107 --> 00:12:54.542
<i>-A round of applause!</i>
-[people cheering]

210
00:13:00.047 --> 00:13:01.583
[muffled thud]

211
00:13:02.016 --> 00:13:03.851
-[man on microphone]
<i>Did you see that? What a...</i>
-[indistinct]

212
00:13:03.984 --> 00:13:05.419
-[man] Happy to be here.
-[Henriette] So. look
who's here.

213
00:13:07.121 --> 00:13:08.389
-[Johanne chuckles]
-Jeez!

214
00:13:09.290 --> 00:13:12.426
-Hey. it's been
a while. quite a while.
-[Johanne] Yeah. really long.

215
00:13:12.560 --> 00:13:14.128
-About three years.
-Three years?

216
00:13:14.261 --> 00:13:15.829
-No way! It must be
-Uh. could be. Yeah.

217
00:13:15.963 --> 00:13:17.131
more like. seven.

218
00:13:17.264 --> 00:13:18.499
-[chuckles]
-[Johanne] Probably...

219
00:13:18.733 --> 00:13:22.269
Hey. Maria! Come
and meet your old babysitter!

220
00:13:23.070 --> 00:13:24.739
Uh. so what are you doing here?

221
00:13:25.272 --> 00:13:27.742
-I'm here for an inspection.
-Ah.

222
00:13:27.908 --> 00:13:30.377
-An inspection? Huh.
-[Johanne] Yeah.

223
00:13:31.845 --> 00:13:32.946
[chuckles] Hi!

224
00:13:33.380 --> 00:13:35.517
-My God. Maria.
you're all grown up.
-Hi!

225
00:13:35.684 --> 00:13:37.818
-Do you recognize her? Huh?
-[Maria] Um...

226
00:13:37.951 --> 00:13:40.888
-[Henriette] Ring a bell?
-You're working
at Marine Research center?

227
00:13:41.021 --> 00:13:42.923
Yeah. That's right. yes.

228
00:13:43.057 --> 00:13:44.626
[vehicle honking]

229
00:13:45.092 --> 00:13:46.728
-[Maria] Uh. see you.
-Sure thing.

230
00:13:47.294 --> 00:13:49.430
[chuckles]
She's a dedicated young lady.

231
00:13:49.564 --> 00:13:51.065
I have to go
take that picture now.

232
00:13:51.198 --> 00:13:52.966
-Mm-hmm.
-Take care.

233
00:13:53.768 --> 00:13:55.035
Good to see you!

234
00:13:55.169 --> 00:13:57.071
[man speaking indistinctly
on microphone]

235
00:13:57.471 --> 00:13:59.674
So. um. can I borrow you a sec?

236
00:13:59.808 --> 00:14:01.175
Of course.

237
00:14:02.644 --> 00:14:05.079
-[machinery whirring]
-[suspenseful music]

238
00:14:15.322 --> 00:14:17.891
[Henriette] They've been
popping up across the fjord.

239
00:14:20.361 --> 00:14:22.363
These must've been really deep.

240
00:14:22.863 --> 00:14:24.898
All the buoys have deflated.

241
00:14:29.671 --> 00:14:31.338
[Henriette]
That's several tons of nets.

242
00:14:31.706 --> 00:14:33.575
How could they have
move around like this?

243
00:14:34.875 --> 00:14:36.944
I'm gonna check with my people.
[soft chuckle]

244
00:14:39.614 --> 00:14:41.281
[seagulls squawking]

245
00:14:41.982 --> 00:14:43.984
This is where we were filming.

246
00:14:44.918 --> 00:14:46.987
It's crazy you blew the whistle.

247
00:14:47.655 --> 00:14:49.123
What's crazy about that?

248
00:14:51.191 --> 00:14:54.361
It's her father. man.
That takes real guts.

249
00:14:57.665 --> 00:14:59.634
Is your father who
runs the fish farm?

250
00:15:00.000 --> 00:15:01.235
Yeah.

251
00:15:02.670 --> 00:15:03.738
Wow.

252
00:15:04.204 --> 00:15:06.808
So. how many views
does the video have?

253
00:15:07.575 --> 00:15:10.043
Dude. you got to stop nagging
about those views already.

254
00:15:10.177 --> 00:15:11.880
A bunch of fat girls
scrolling through TikTok

255
00:15:12.012 --> 00:15:13.848
and seeing the videos
means nothing.

256
00:15:13.981 --> 00:15:15.650
You really think
it means anything?

257
00:15:15.884 --> 00:15:17.284
That's not why we're here. man.

258
00:15:18.352 --> 00:15:20.722
-We're here
to do something. aren't we?
-Yeah.

259
00:15:20.855 --> 00:15:22.256
And to make a difference?

260
00:15:23.558 --> 00:15:25.292
Have you heard about
David Suzuki?

261
00:15:27.294 --> 00:15:29.263
Do you know who David Suzuki is?

262
00:15:29.963 --> 00:15:31.498
No. who's that?

263
00:15:31.699 --> 00:15:32.966
[scoffs]

264
00:15:33.400 --> 00:15:34.536
[exhales]

265
00:15:37.137 --> 00:15:39.173
[man]
You know who Greta Thunberg is?

266
00:15:40.909 --> 00:15:43.944
Greta Thunberg comes up
to David Suzuki's bellybutton.

267
00:15:45.112 --> 00:15:46.648
Alright. let's do it then.

268
00:15:48.215 --> 00:15:49.651
I wanna grab a beer.

269
00:15:52.219 --> 00:15:54.421
[Georg on radio]
<i>There's plenty of cake left.</i>

270
00:15:54.556 --> 00:15:55.723
[chuckles]

271
00:15:56.223 --> 00:15:59.193
<i>Did you know that the Japanese</i>
<i>actually don't like marzipan?</i>

272
00:15:59.326 --> 00:16:01.696
[chuckles then grunts]

273
00:16:03.330 --> 00:16:05.232
[muffled upbeat pop music]

274
00:16:07.167 --> 00:16:08.202
[sighs]

275
00:16:08.536 --> 00:16:10.638
Okay. Georg.
you can turn it back on.

276
00:16:11.806 --> 00:16:13.106
<i>Okay. same strength?</i>

277
00:16:13.240 --> 00:16:15.375
Take the frequency
down two notches.

278
00:16:15.910 --> 00:16:17.411
<i>Okay. copy that.</i>

279
00:16:19.581 --> 00:16:22.316
-[pop music stops]
-[keyboard clacking]

280
00:16:23.317 --> 00:16:24.819
[computer beeping]

281
00:16:24.953 --> 00:16:26.186
[suspenseful music]

282
00:16:27.789 --> 00:16:28.957
[machinery whirring]

283
00:16:29.089 --> 00:16:30.859
[computer voice]
<i>Module 4. active.</i>

284
00:16:31.258 --> 00:16:34.127
[mechanical buzzing]

285
00:16:42.971 --> 00:16:45.472
[buzzing slowly muffles]

286
00:16:45.840 --> 00:16:47.575
[muffled rumble]

287
00:16:49.009 --> 00:16:51.178
[high-pitched muffled ring]

288
00:16:55.115 --> 00:16:57.251
[high-pitched ring]

289
00:16:58.686 --> 00:17:01.723
[computer voice] <i>Attention.</i>
<i>Reduce Sonic Lice intensity.</i>

290
00:17:01.923 --> 00:17:04.024
<i>Attention. Reduce Sonic Lice--</i>

291
00:17:04.157 --> 00:17:06.026
-[computer beeps]
<i>-Deactivating alarm.</i>

292
00:17:07.027 --> 00:17:08.228
[seagulls squawking]

293
00:17:08.362 --> 00:17:10.397
[boat's motor rumbling]

294
00:17:12.266 --> 00:17:13.801
[soft melancholic music]

295
00:17:19.674 --> 00:17:22.109
Look. look at that shit
over there.

296
00:17:22.744 --> 00:17:25.813
You have to shut it down
before it's too late.

297
00:17:28.448 --> 00:17:30.484
The fjord isn't
like it used to be.

298
00:17:33.688 --> 00:17:35.790
You know.
I've missed you too. Olav.

299
00:17:35.924 --> 00:17:37.725
[Olav chuckles]

300
00:17:38.458 --> 00:17:40.494
[muffled high-pitch ringing]

301
00:17:45.533 --> 00:17:46.768
-[music ends abruptly]
-[case clanks]

302
00:17:48.970 --> 00:17:50.270
[boat honking]

303
00:17:50.404 --> 00:17:51.806
Thanks for the ride!

304
00:17:56.711 --> 00:17:57.745
[sighs]

305
00:17:58.078 --> 00:17:59.581
[melancholic music continues]

306
00:18:03.417 --> 00:18:05.452
[indistinct rumble]

307
00:18:14.261 --> 00:18:16.698
[Georg distantly] 'Cause. you
know. if you use 98 octane.

308
00:18:16.831 --> 00:18:18.800
you fuck with the carburetor.
the spark plugs.

309
00:18:18.933 --> 00:18:21.368
I mean. you get
soot all over that shit.

310
00:18:22.837 --> 00:18:25.039
How long have you stored the
engine with that shit. man?

311
00:18:25.172 --> 00:18:27.240
It rusts from the inside.

312
00:18:27.742 --> 00:18:29.711
It should've been
changed ages ago.

313
00:18:29.844 --> 00:18:31.646
-I mean. what are you
guys doing?
-[Erik] <i>Thanks. Georg.</i>

314
00:18:31.779 --> 00:18:33.948
<i>-any more good suggestions?</i>
-Just saying. you're never gonna

315
00:18:34.082 --> 00:18:35.683
-get that working.
-[door opens in background]

316
00:18:35.817 --> 00:18:37.685
[Erik] <i>If Jostein calls.</i>
<i>I'm in the workshop.</i>

317
00:18:39.087 --> 00:18:41.121
[music continues]

318
00:18:47.795 --> 00:18:49.162
Erik?

319
00:18:54.434 --> 00:18:57.105
[pull cord yanked]

320
00:18:57.304 --> 00:18:58.706
[Erik groaning]

321
00:19:08.616 --> 00:19:09.817
Hi. Erik.

322
00:19:10.450 --> 00:19:12.120
[music fades]

323
00:19:12.520 --> 00:19:14.922
I tried to call you
on the way up. but I. um...

324
00:19:15.422 --> 00:19:16.591
What are you doing here?

325
00:19:16.724 --> 00:19:18.593
I work for Marine Research.

326
00:19:19.192 --> 00:19:21.161
I'm here for an inspection.

327
00:19:22.162 --> 00:19:23.598
Right.

328
00:19:23.831 --> 00:19:24.899
Uh-huh.

329
00:19:25.033 --> 00:19:26.734
You're running
the show over here. I see.

330
00:19:26.868 --> 00:19:28.002
That's pretty cool.

331
00:19:28.703 --> 00:19:31.939
[Jostein] <i>Erik? Listen.</i>
<i>The inspector's</i>
<i>on their way out here.</i>

332
00:19:32.073 --> 00:19:33.708
<i>and I recommend to please--</i>

333
00:19:34.776 --> 00:19:35.576
[Georg grunting]

334
00:19:35.710 --> 00:19:38.412
Hey. Jostein called. uh...

335
00:19:38.546 --> 00:19:41.314
Say hello to Johanne.
She's here for an inspection.

336
00:19:42.382 --> 00:19:44.752
-Hi! Uh. hi.
-This here is Georg.

337
00:19:44.886 --> 00:19:46.020
Johanne.

338
00:19:46.821 --> 00:19:48.455
[Erik] Well. I don't know
where you wanna start?

339
00:19:48.723 --> 00:19:51.224
Georg. why don't you tag along
and show her around the place?

340
00:19:51.559 --> 00:19:54.327
Yeah. okay just...
[clears throat] follow me.

341
00:19:55.328 --> 00:19:57.197
[intriguing music]

342
00:19:57.532 --> 00:19:59.499
[footsteps receding]

343
00:20:01.301 --> 00:20:03.838
Well. the whole fish farm
is assembled

344
00:20:03.971 --> 00:20:07.742
out of all sorts of modules
from various old warships.

345
00:20:08.042 --> 00:20:09.342
So... here's the lab.

346
00:20:10.078 --> 00:20:11.311
Okay.

347
00:20:13.047 --> 00:20:16.349
[Georg] It's run down.
but the equipment is brand new.

348
00:20:17.819 --> 00:20:20.287
The steel is 35 millimeters
at its thickest

349
00:20:20.420 --> 00:20:22.824
and then we'll find
starboard here.

350
00:20:23.024 --> 00:20:24.257
Over here.

351
00:20:25.026 --> 00:20:26.426
-Sorry. I...
-Yeah.

352
00:20:26.561 --> 00:20:28.295
[grunting]
...just need to get this.

353
00:20:29.163 --> 00:20:30.531
There we go.

354
00:20:34.569 --> 00:20:36.704
This is actually
an old captain's cabin.

355
00:20:36.838 --> 00:20:38.305
Okay...

356
00:20:40.174 --> 00:20:41.776
-Yeah.
-[Johanne] Thank you.

357
00:20:43.911 --> 00:20:45.580
I've got the technicals
on one and two.

358
00:20:45.713 --> 00:20:47.247
-so just...
-Uh...

359
00:20:48.816 --> 00:20:50.518
[music continues]

360
00:20:53.054 --> 00:20:54.354
[Erik] Is she staying here?

361
00:20:54.789 --> 00:20:55.923
Hey. yeah.

362
00:20:56.924 --> 00:20:57.959
Right.

363
00:21:01.129 --> 00:21:02.196
Let me know when you're ready.

364
00:21:02.329 --> 00:21:03.564
[clears throat]

365
00:21:10.370 --> 00:21:11.773
[music continues]

366
00:21:26.419 --> 00:21:27.622
[seagulls squawking]

367
00:21:30.591 --> 00:21:31.826
[music fades]

368
00:21:37.497 --> 00:21:39.000
[muffled underwater ambiance]

369
00:21:48.408 --> 00:21:49.911
[water splashes abruptly]

370
00:21:51.012 --> 00:21:51.946
[Erik sighing]

371
00:21:52.079 --> 00:21:53.313
[chuckles]

372
00:21:56.117 --> 00:21:57.317
What can you hear?

373
00:21:57.785 --> 00:21:59.954
-I heard you.
-[Erik chuckles]

374
00:22:00.221 --> 00:22:01.454
[Johanne chuckles]

375
00:22:03.825 --> 00:22:05.425
But what I meant was...

376
00:22:08.863 --> 00:22:10.330
...did you find anything...

377
00:22:11.065 --> 00:22:12.365
...to get us in trouble?

378
00:22:12.867 --> 00:22:14.001
Not yet.

379
00:22:14.235 --> 00:22:15.870
[pensive music]

380
00:22:20.575 --> 00:22:21.609
Wanna listen?

381
00:22:21.876 --> 00:22:24.111
-[grunts]
-[Johanne chuckles]

382
00:22:24.579 --> 00:22:26.047
[both laugh]

383
00:22:30.284 --> 00:22:31.619
-[Erik] Alright.
-Take this.

384
00:22:39.426 --> 00:22:40.661
[soft chuckle]

385
00:22:48.569 --> 00:22:49.804
[soft chuckle]

386
00:22:56.077 --> 00:22:57.545
Why did you really come?

387
00:23:00.615 --> 00:23:02.516
[seagulls squawking
at a distance]

388
00:23:05.452 --> 00:23:06.821
Erik.

389
00:23:08.089 --> 00:23:09.456
Erik.

390
00:23:14.161 --> 00:23:16.097
[eerie whirring]

391
00:23:16.797 --> 00:23:18.498
You still in or what? Huh?

392
00:23:18.766 --> 00:23:20.268
[soft radio music]

393
00:23:20.400 --> 00:23:21.903
[soft clinking]

394
00:23:30.244 --> 00:23:33.381
-We agreed
on this yesterday. right?
-But what about the wild salmon?

395
00:23:33.514 --> 00:23:35.182
The wild salmon
are fucked anyway.

396
00:23:35.316 --> 00:23:36.550
[scoffs]

397
00:23:38.286 --> 00:23:39.486
Let's just wait.

398
00:23:40.087 --> 00:23:42.523
Johanne will help us
shut the fish farm down.

399
00:23:44.258 --> 00:23:45.593
[sighs]

400
00:23:47.295 --> 00:23:50.031
Well. enjoy your eggs. kids.
I'm going for a swim.

401
00:23:55.169 --> 00:23:56.469
[crab skittering]

402
00:23:56.737 --> 00:23:58.506
[suspenseful music]

403
00:23:59.807 --> 00:24:01.776
[upbeat muffled music]

404
00:24:03.978 --> 00:24:05.813
[music continues on speakers]

405
00:24:05.947 --> 00:24:08.549
[radio announcer]
<i>In Vangsnes in the Sognefjord</i>

406
00:24:08.683 --> 00:24:10.785
<i>two people have gone missing.</i>

407
00:24:12.019 --> 00:24:14.221
[Henriette] Alright.
there's no problem with that.

408
00:24:17.258 --> 00:24:20.127
-Do you want coffee?
-Yes. please.

409
00:24:21.429 --> 00:24:23.331
[melancholic music]

410
00:24:24.398 --> 00:24:26.367
[Henriette] Jostein.
can't you just let them go up

411
00:24:26.499 --> 00:24:28.169
in the seaplane by themselves?

412
00:24:37.111 --> 00:24:39.814
Do you have
to be there all the time?

413
00:24:43.483 --> 00:24:44.952
[Maria laughs]

414
00:24:46.087 --> 00:24:48.756
[Maria speaking indistinctly]

415
00:24:51.726 --> 00:24:53.294
[door opens]

416
00:24:53.461 --> 00:24:55.830
-[Maria laughs]
-[man] ... yes. but it's true.

417
00:24:56.864 --> 00:24:57.832
-[Johanne] Hi.
-Hi.

418
00:24:57.965 --> 00:24:59.200
-[both chuckle]
-Hi.

419
00:24:59.333 --> 00:25:00.401
[toilet flushes]

420
00:25:00.634 --> 00:25:02.003
-[Maria] What's up?
-[man grunts]

421
00:25:02.136 --> 00:25:03.604
[Henriette] Hey. Maria.
where are you. honey?

422
00:25:04.338 --> 00:25:07.208
-[man] I'd wait a bit
to use the toilet.
-[Maria] Mo-- Hey. Mom...

423
00:25:07.742 --> 00:25:08.943
[Henriette]
But I need to know this things.

424
00:25:09.076 --> 00:25:10.911
I invited people for lunch.

425
00:25:12.446 --> 00:25:14.281
That's exactly what annoys me.

426
00:25:14.548 --> 00:25:16.517
Maybe you should
move to Japan. huh?

427
00:25:16.884 --> 00:25:18.986
You know that?
You're never here anyway.

428
00:25:19.420 --> 00:25:20.988
Yeah. I do mean that.

429
00:25:21.522 --> 00:25:24.058
-You always promise me
the same...
-Is that your boat?

430
00:25:24.959 --> 00:25:26.227
-Yeah.
-[Henriette] Jostein...

431
00:25:26.360 --> 00:25:28.262
-[Johanne] It's really nice.
-Thank you.

432
00:25:28.996 --> 00:25:31.699
I got it from my dad.
for my confirmation.

433
00:25:31.966 --> 00:25:34.902
[Henriette] Well. there has to
be a way. figure it out.

434
00:25:35.403 --> 00:25:36.505
What's it called?

435
00:25:37.004 --> 00:25:39.607
It doesn't have a name. for now.

436
00:25:39.740 --> 00:25:41.475
But I'm thinking maybe
something with

437
00:25:41.609 --> 00:25:43.411
-Stella or Star.
-[Henriette speaking
indistinctly in background]

438
00:25:43.911 --> 00:25:45.479
I saw the video you sent.

439
00:25:46.047 --> 00:25:47.615
-You did?
-[Johanne] Mm-hmm.

440
00:25:47.748 --> 00:25:49.617
-Is that why you're here?
-Mm-hmm.

441
00:25:49.784 --> 00:25:51.018
[suspenseful music]

442
00:25:51.419 --> 00:25:52.553
And what do you think?

443
00:25:52.953 --> 00:25:54.555
What do you think?

444
00:25:55.990 --> 00:25:58.392
[chuckles] I mean. the fish are
acting absolutely insane.

445
00:25:58.527 --> 00:26:00.127
-[Johanne] Mm-hmm.
-so they can't even navigate.

446
00:26:00.261 --> 00:26:02.196
-[Johanne] Yeah.
-Everything is fucked.

447
00:26:03.898 --> 00:26:06.467
So. when are you going to shut
down that damn fish farm?

448
00:26:07.068 --> 00:26:08.936
I'm not the one who does that.

449
00:26:10.638 --> 00:26:12.339
But you saw what happened
in the video!

450
00:26:12.573 --> 00:26:14.041
I write reports
and I log things.

451
00:26:14.175 --> 00:26:16.177
-but that's
someone else's job. I--
-[scoffs]

452
00:26:16.410 --> 00:26:18.779
So. there was no point in
sounding the alarm.

453
00:26:19.847 --> 00:26:22.583
Let me say. Maria. I think it's
amazing that you care so much--

454
00:26:22.716 --> 00:26:25.119
Oh. shut up.
you're all fucking corrupt.

455
00:26:29.558 --> 00:26:32.326
[sighs] Yeah... that's my life.

456
00:26:32.460 --> 00:26:34.028
[upbeat music]

457
00:26:40.434 --> 00:26:41.469
How'd it go?

458
00:26:41.602 --> 00:26:43.337
[Maria] Ugh. it went like shit.

459
00:26:45.039 --> 00:26:47.108
-[music stops]
-[seagulls squawking]

460
00:26:52.146 --> 00:26:54.415
Salmon mortality
increased in recent weeks.

461
00:26:54.549 --> 00:26:55.983
Yes. and by a few percent.

462
00:26:56.150 --> 00:26:58.686
But the salmon lice numbers
have gone down.

463
00:26:58.819 --> 00:27:01.122
Are there many disoriented fish
in the area?

464
00:27:01.255 --> 00:27:02.890
-No.
-[male voice on video] ... <i>that</i>
<i>attaches itself</i>

465
00:27:03.023 --> 00:27:04.492
<i>to a host and kills it.</i>

466
00:27:04.725 --> 00:27:08.095
<i>Sonic Lice is the solution.</i>
<i>Using state-of-the-art</i>

467
00:27:08.229 --> 00:27:09.697
<i>-technology to safely</i>
-[Johanne] Did you make that
yourself?

468
00:27:09.830 --> 00:27:11.265
<i>-remove the lice.</i>
-[Georg] Yeah.

469
00:27:11.398 --> 00:27:13.334
<i>our new transducers</i>
<i>are using sound waves</i>

470
00:27:13.467 --> 00:27:14.835
<i>to remove the parasite.</i>

471
00:27:15.302 --> 00:27:17.606
<i>For a healthier</i>
<i>salmon industry.</i>

472
00:27:17.738 --> 00:27:20.107
<i>-through our cutting-edge</i>
<i>technology.</i>
-[somber music]

473
00:27:20.241 --> 00:27:23.512
<i>we are creating green jobs</i>
<i>in Vangsnes.</i>

474
00:27:23.878 --> 00:27:25.779
[computer beeping]

475
00:27:26.714 --> 00:27:28.782
I need the logs for Sonic Lice.

476
00:27:30.619 --> 00:27:32.253
That might take some time.

477
00:27:35.089 --> 00:27:37.358
It's the fucking Matrix.
this thing.

478
00:27:37.559 --> 00:27:39.393
That's fine by me. I'll be here.

479
00:27:40.261 --> 00:27:41.395
I'll take this.

480
00:27:42.763 --> 00:27:43.998
[music fades]

481
00:27:44.331 --> 00:27:46.033
[classical music]

482
00:27:47.434 --> 00:27:52.840
And next year. we are planning
to triple our production.

483
00:27:54.643 --> 00:27:56.143
[speaking Japanese]

484
00:27:56.343 --> 00:27:58.946
Of course. we need. uh. to get
our applications approved.

485
00:27:59.079 --> 00:28:01.650
And. uh. there are a lot of
regulations.

486
00:28:01.782 --> 00:28:03.417
-Uh. and we really
-[inaudible]

487
00:28:03.552 --> 00:28:05.554
want to keep the high quality.

488
00:28:05.686 --> 00:28:06.787
The highest.

489
00:28:06.987 --> 00:28:09.156
[woman translating]

490
00:28:15.763 --> 00:28:19.233
Are you a small fish
or a big fish?

491
00:28:22.102 --> 00:28:23.704
-[chuckles]
-[cellphone buzzing]

492
00:28:24.338 --> 00:28:25.973
[laughs]

493
00:28:26.974 --> 00:28:28.409
Excuse me.

494
00:28:30.444 --> 00:28:32.213
I'm a bit busy right now.
Is it important?

495
00:28:32.346 --> 00:28:35.115
Yes. One module is down.
and we're having an inspection.

496
00:28:37.084 --> 00:28:38.852
[Jostein] <i>Okay.</i>
<i>but you'll fix it. right?</i>

497
00:28:39.420 --> 00:28:41.121
-You fix everything.
-[Erik] <i>But Jostein.</i>
<i>we need time</i>

498
00:28:41.255 --> 00:28:42.557
<i>to organize things. I--</i>

499
00:28:42.691 --> 00:28:44.325
-Look. I think--
-[phone line cuts]

500
00:28:47.562 --> 00:28:49.396
What exactly is she doing?

501
00:28:50.864 --> 00:28:52.433
[Erik] Interviewing the salmon.

502
00:28:54.603 --> 00:28:56.203
Asking them how they feel.

503
00:28:59.974 --> 00:29:01.141
Erik...

504
00:29:01.308 --> 00:29:03.744
she asked
for the Sonic Lice log.

505
00:29:05.846 --> 00:29:07.114
Give it to her.

506
00:29:08.015 --> 00:29:09.883
-[suspenseful music]
-Mmm.

507
00:29:11.318 --> 00:29:13.454
-[Erik] Turn your walkie on!
-[door opens]

508
00:29:15.055 --> 00:29:16.957
-[door closes]
-[radio turns on]

509
00:29:18.459 --> 00:29:20.894
-[classical music continues]
-Uh. sorry about that. [sighs]

510
00:29:22.396 --> 00:29:23.665
So. Jostein...

511
00:29:24.064 --> 00:29:26.467
how many fjords
do you have in Norway?

512
00:29:32.106 --> 00:29:33.841
How many do you want?

513
00:29:36.578 --> 00:29:38.445
[muffled classical music]

514
00:29:38.580 --> 00:29:40.515
[music turns eerie]

515
00:30:02.970 --> 00:30:05.039
[electrical beeping]

516
00:30:09.611 --> 00:30:11.312
[notification chimes]

517
00:30:19.654 --> 00:30:23.157
-[phone chimes]
-[Johanne] Report inspection
Western Salmon Vangsnes.

518
00:30:23.457 --> 00:30:26.594
<i>Simulation of Sonic Lice</i>
<i>on live salmon heart.</i>

519
00:30:31.131 --> 00:30:33.367
[keyboard clacking]

520
00:30:37.438 --> 00:30:40.407
<i>Normal frequency.</i>
<i>no measurable effect.</i>

521
00:30:40.908 --> 00:30:42.476
[electric buzzing]

522
00:30:47.649 --> 00:30:49.651
<i>Frequency above the gut</i>
<i>off-limit.</i>

523
00:30:49.784 --> 00:30:52.086
<i>immediately affects</i>
<i>the heart rhythm.</i>

524
00:30:52.986 --> 00:30:54.221
[buzzing intensifies]

525
00:30:59.093 --> 00:31:01.730
[computer voice] <i>Above blocking</i>
<i>level. above blocking level.</i>

526
00:31:01.862 --> 00:31:03.230
[wet blast]

527
00:31:05.032 --> 00:31:06.601
[sustained beeping]

528
00:31:06.735 --> 00:31:09.002
[Johanne] <i>At max level we get</i>
<i>soft tissue collapse</i>

529
00:31:09.136 --> 00:31:11.105
<i>and 100% mortality.</i>

530
00:31:11.606 --> 00:31:12.973
[electric buzzing]

531
00:31:14.776 --> 00:31:16.544
-[heavy thud]
-[buzzing stops]

532
00:31:17.277 --> 00:31:19.279
-[pop music]
-[computer beeping]

533
00:31:22.082 --> 00:31:23.618
[alarm blaring]

534
00:31:26.253 --> 00:31:28.422
-Erik. you have to
bring up four.
-[radio beeps]

535
00:31:29.289 --> 00:31:31.191
[Erik] <i>It's on its way!</i>
<i>It's on its way...</i>

536
00:31:39.233 --> 00:31:40.735
[thunder rumbling]

537
00:31:40.934 --> 00:31:42.269
[Erik] Fuck.

538
00:31:45.673 --> 00:31:47.040
[metallic rattling]

539
00:31:47.441 --> 00:31:48.442
[scoffs]

540
00:31:49.076 --> 00:31:50.512
I'll give you some light.

541
00:31:53.748 --> 00:31:54.816
Under there. Thanks.

542
00:31:54.948 --> 00:31:56.216
Yeah. I got you.

543
00:31:56.350 --> 00:31:58.085
[Erik] I need to replace the
transducer.

544
00:31:58.385 --> 00:32:00.154
It's crazy to see it like this.

545
00:32:00.287 --> 00:32:03.625
And to think of all the hours
we spent on it. Remember?

546
00:32:04.592 --> 00:32:07.194
It took a year to finish the
transducer after you left.

547
00:32:07.729 --> 00:32:10.297
About four years to get this
module done.

548
00:32:11.365 --> 00:32:13.333
-Hard work pays off.
-[chuckles]

549
00:32:13.467 --> 00:32:14.869
-Yeah.
-[Erik] Mm-hmm.

550
00:32:15.002 --> 00:32:16.504
so that means it works. then?

551
00:32:17.471 --> 00:32:18.405
Huh?

552
00:32:18.540 --> 00:32:20.274
Does it really work as
it should?

553
00:32:20.941 --> 00:32:22.209
It got approved. right?

554
00:32:22.943 --> 00:32:26.714
Yeah. but what about the
threshold values.
You figured all that out?

555
00:32:26.947 --> 00:32:28.215
It works now.

556
00:32:31.753 --> 00:32:33.053
[metallic thud]

557
00:32:41.228 --> 00:32:42.262
[suspenseful music]

558
00:32:42.564 --> 00:32:45.065
-Can you open it on that side?
-Okay.

559
00:32:45.966 --> 00:32:48.335
-[Erik] Push it twice. thanks.
-[Johanne] Yup.

560
00:32:51.806 --> 00:32:53.040
[soft thud]

561
00:33:00.615 --> 00:33:02.149
[intriguing music]

562
00:33:02.650 --> 00:33:03.685
What the fuck?

563
00:33:04.752 --> 00:33:06.386
[thunder rumbling]

564
00:33:15.897 --> 00:33:17.532
[wet crushing]

565
00:33:19.834 --> 00:33:21.101
[Johanne] Oh my God!

566
00:33:22.770 --> 00:33:24.137
Let me...

567
00:33:27.040 --> 00:33:28.576
[music continues faintly]

568
00:33:31.746 --> 00:33:34.047
[soft. wet crushing]

569
00:33:44.826 --> 00:33:46.761
[Johanne on recording]
<i>Discovery of unknown species</i>

570
00:33:46.895 --> 00:33:48.863
<i>in Sonic Lice Module four.</i>

571
00:33:49.396 --> 00:33:51.900
<i>Possibly attracted</i>
<i>by the sound itself.</i>

572
00:33:52.232 --> 00:33:54.201
<i>Looks like</i>
<i>a deep-water organism.</i>

573
00:33:54.334 --> 00:33:56.538
<i>Abnormal amino acid levels.</i>

574
00:33:59.541 --> 00:34:01.141
<i>Never seen anything like it.</i>

575
00:34:01.275 --> 00:34:02.510
[wet squeezing]

576
00:34:06.179 --> 00:34:07.549
[grunts]

577
00:34:13.988 --> 00:34:15.222
Bioluminescence?

578
00:34:15.355 --> 00:34:16.858
[Johanne] Looks like it. yeah.

579
00:34:17.926 --> 00:34:19.894
But it's hard to determine
if it has the same

580
00:34:20.028 --> 00:34:21.896
characteristics as a parasite.

581
00:34:22.964 --> 00:34:25.332
In that case.
the host must be enormous.

582
00:34:25.767 --> 00:34:27.635
So. you've discovered
a new species?

583
00:34:27.769 --> 00:34:28.803
[chuckles]

584
00:34:29.102 --> 00:34:30.605
[Erik chuckles]

585
00:34:34.709 --> 00:34:35.777
You have some--

586
00:34:41.916 --> 00:34:43.718
[water running]

587
00:34:43.885 --> 00:34:46.086
[music continues]

588
00:34:51.526 --> 00:34:52.560
[grunts]

589
00:35:02.436 --> 00:35:04.438
[intriguing music continues]

590
00:35:12.145 --> 00:35:13.581
[man] Do you need
help out there?

591
00:35:13.715 --> 00:35:15.382
[Henriette] No. just pull back.

592
00:35:16.618 --> 00:35:19.219
-[police officer]
<i>It's the missing jet ski.</i>
-Thanks.

593
00:35:19.520 --> 00:35:21.723
[machinery whirring]

594
00:35:21.889 --> 00:35:23.256
[indistinct conversations]

595
00:35:23.457 --> 00:35:24.993
[man 2] Looks in rough shape.

596
00:35:25.359 --> 00:35:28.195
Champ. don't get too close.
come back here.

597
00:35:36.269 --> 00:35:38.506
[pop music]

598
00:35:40.207 --> 00:35:42.543
[computer beeping]

599
00:35:46.547 --> 00:35:48.148
Jesus. look at that.

600
00:35:48.281 --> 00:35:50.217
[somber music]

601
00:35:53.521 --> 00:35:54.889
We need to dive. man.

602
00:35:57.925 --> 00:35:59.326
Erik. I have to--

603
00:36:00.494 --> 00:36:02.730
[beeping continues]

604
00:36:07.434 --> 00:36:09.771
[music increases]

605
00:36:18.513 --> 00:36:20.380
[Georg]
Must be a porpoise that got in.

606
00:36:26.420 --> 00:36:28.221
[breathing through mask]

607
00:36:29.757 --> 00:36:30.858
[Erik] Okay?

608
00:36:33.326 --> 00:36:34.662
Ready. Georg?

609
00:36:35.897 --> 00:36:36.964
[muffled splash]

610
00:36:52.412 --> 00:36:54.982
[suspenseful music]

611
00:37:11.231 --> 00:37:12.667
[rope tightening]

612
00:37:26.346 --> 00:37:28.015
[eerie sting]

613
00:37:36.289 --> 00:37:37.592
Why did you have
to bring them up?

614
00:37:37.725 --> 00:37:40.327
They were being eaten.
for fuck's sake!

615
00:37:41.129 --> 00:37:42.496
They're in the cold room.

616
00:37:44.632 --> 00:37:46.466
[music fades lightly]

617
00:37:51.973 --> 00:37:54.374
[Henriette] Looks like it's
the two missing tourists.

618
00:37:55.176 --> 00:37:56.878
Mm... [grunts]

619
00:37:57.277 --> 00:37:58.579
[sighs]

620
00:37:59.412 --> 00:38:01.783
-Erik. lights off. please?
-[door closes]

621
00:38:02.482 --> 00:38:03.718
[light switch clicks]

622
00:38:07.354 --> 00:38:08.756
Look at this.

623
00:38:10.290 --> 00:38:11.893
[water dripping]

624
00:38:13.628 --> 00:38:16.230
-[Henriette] What's that?
-[Johanne] It's bioluminescence.

625
00:38:16.363 --> 00:38:20.467
Bacteria that reacts to an
enzyme and becomes luminescent.

626
00:38:21.569 --> 00:38:23.671
-Have you seen milky seas?
-Yeah.

627
00:38:23.805 --> 00:38:25.506
This is just like that.

628
00:38:28.308 --> 00:38:30.343
-From the fish farm?
-No.

629
00:38:31.012 --> 00:38:33.848
This must stem from an animal
deep in the ocean.

630
00:38:33.981 --> 00:38:36.951
And with this amount of
luciferin. the animal must be...

631
00:38:37.350 --> 00:38:38.686
big.

632
00:38:40.521 --> 00:38:42.723
What could trigger
such a high production?

633
00:38:43.124 --> 00:38:46.928
Many species produce more
luciferin if they. for example.

634
00:38:47.228 --> 00:38:50.064
are spawning
or feel threatened by something.

635
00:38:50.832 --> 00:38:53.067
[music intensifying gradually]

636
00:39:00.975 --> 00:39:02.877
[skittering]

637
00:39:06.547 --> 00:39:08.549
-[door closes]
-[soft music]

638
00:39:09.951 --> 00:39:11.052
Hey. you.

639
00:39:11.418 --> 00:39:12.753
[Jostein] Hi.

640
00:39:14.421 --> 00:39:15.756
Hey!

641
00:39:16.190 --> 00:39:17.525
How did it go today?

642
00:39:18.192 --> 00:39:19.327
Did they seem happy?

643
00:39:19.594 --> 00:39:21.394
Yeah. "How'd it go?" is right.

644
00:39:22.563 --> 00:39:23.698
[Henriette] Bad?

645
00:39:23.831 --> 00:39:25.333
[Jostein] Well. apparently...

646
00:39:26.067 --> 00:39:28.769
they wanna make the project
ten times bigger.

647
00:39:30.171 --> 00:39:31.371
[both chuckle]

648
00:39:31.505 --> 00:39:32.940
-Yes?
-[Henriette] Congratulations!

649
00:39:33.074 --> 00:39:35.309
[Jostein] We're signing at the
restaurant tomorrow.

650
00:39:35.843 --> 00:39:38.012
-[chuckles] Thanks.
-[glasses clink]

651
00:39:39.146 --> 00:39:40.615
-[distant door opens]
-[glass clinking]

652
00:39:41.381 --> 00:39:43.050
-Mm!
-Mm. this is good.

653
00:39:43.184 --> 00:39:45.720
-[Maria] Hey.
-Hey! Whe-- Where are you going
with that?

654
00:39:46.187 --> 00:39:47.521
Gonna dump it in the fjord.

655
00:39:47.655 --> 00:39:49.023
[Henriette sighs] If you're
gonna steal it.

656
00:39:49.156 --> 00:39:50.558
could you at least not do it in
front of me?

657
00:39:50.691 --> 00:39:52.126
Your mom's a cop.
You have to steal it

658
00:39:52.260 --> 00:39:53.694
-in front of me! [chuckles]
-Oh. gosh.

659
00:39:53.828 --> 00:39:55.428
I know that
you have two grown-up men

660
00:39:55.563 --> 00:39:56.931
down in that boat of yours.

661
00:40:00.268 --> 00:40:02.136
Damn. you look so tired. Mom.

662
00:40:02.637 --> 00:40:03.905
[chuckles]

663
00:40:04.038 --> 00:40:06.774
Couldn't you just support me
once in a while?

664
00:40:07.575 --> 00:40:08.976
-I'm sorry.
-[sighs]

665
00:40:09.944 --> 00:40:12.113
[dramatic. suspenseful music]

666
00:40:14.548 --> 00:40:16.617
[mechanical whirring]

667
00:40:27.561 --> 00:40:29.797
[muffled whirring]

668
00:40:37.838 --> 00:40:40.174
[metallic rattling]

669
00:40:44.979 --> 00:40:46.647
[faint splashes]

670
00:41:00.428 --> 00:41:02.462
[loud splashing]

671
00:41:09.469 --> 00:41:11.105
[somber music]

672
00:41:12.807 --> 00:41:15.009
[indistinct squeaking]

673
00:41:34.929 --> 00:41:36.764
-[high-pitched ringing]
-[muffled rumbling]

674
00:41:38.532 --> 00:41:39.934
[muffled rumbling]

675
00:41:41.936 --> 00:41:43.437
-[distorted rumbling]
-[explosion]

676
00:41:43.571 --> 00:41:45.006
[gasps]

677
00:41:45.139 --> 00:41:46.173
[exhales]

678
00:41:49.543 --> 00:41:51.145
[wet movement]

679
00:42:02.123 --> 00:42:03.958
-[skittering]
-[screaming]

680
00:42:06.160 --> 00:42:08.229
[heavy breathing]

681
00:42:14.135 --> 00:42:16.670
Fuck. Oh. fuck.

682
00:42:16.804 --> 00:42:19.006
[muffled splashing]

683
00:42:23.144 --> 00:42:24.545
-[soft splashing]
-[woman] Yeah!

684
00:42:24.678 --> 00:42:26.080
-You got it.
-[woman 2] Now. you try!

685
00:42:26.213 --> 00:42:28.716
-Go ahead!
-[man] Oh! [laughs]

686
00:42:28.849 --> 00:42:30.519
-Nice. well done!
-[all cheering]

687
00:42:30.651 --> 00:42:32.553
-Nice!
-[man] Woo!

688
00:42:33.654 --> 00:42:35.689
Alright. looks like
she's got it too.

689
00:42:37.825 --> 00:42:40.294
[eerie rumble]

690
00:42:41.796 --> 00:42:44.365
Okay. Vigdis.
now it's your turn.

691
00:42:44.533 --> 00:42:45.566
[pop music on speakers]

692
00:42:45.766 --> 00:42:47.101
Are you ready?

693
00:42:50.938 --> 00:42:53.407
Siri's got you.
Remember to flex your hip.

694
00:42:53.542 --> 00:42:55.176
-Come on. Vigdis!
-[all cheering]

695
00:42:55.342 --> 00:42:57.311
-[woman] You got this.
you got this.
-[man] You got this!

696
00:42:57.445 --> 00:42:59.914
[people cheering]
Vigdis. Vigdis. Vigdis!

697
00:43:07.588 --> 00:43:09.623
[suspenseful music]

698
00:43:11.992 --> 00:43:14.328
[muffled struggling]

699
00:43:15.262 --> 00:43:17.131
[seagulls squawking]

700
00:43:21.102 --> 00:43:22.970
-[eerie rumble]
-[heavy splash]

701
00:43:24.338 --> 00:43:25.372
Vigdis!

702
00:43:28.642 --> 00:43:29.743
[eerie rumble]

703
00:43:30.077 --> 00:43:31.580
-[loud splash]
-[all screaming]

704
00:43:31.946 --> 00:43:34.014
[seagulls squawking]

705
00:43:36.350 --> 00:43:38.385
[device beeping]

706
00:43:41.088 --> 00:43:43.090
[muffled high-pitched whirring]

707
00:43:51.398 --> 00:43:52.867
[deep rumble]

708
00:43:56.904 --> 00:43:58.806
[seagulls squawking]

709
00:43:59.306 --> 00:44:00.542
[music fades]

710
00:44:00.674 --> 00:44:02.176
[constant rumbling]

711
00:44:14.421 --> 00:44:15.590
[somber music]

712
00:44:15.990 --> 00:44:18.325
[Johanne] How old were you
when that stuff happened?

713
00:44:18.959 --> 00:44:22.229
Mm. I was maybe ten
or 11 years old.

714
00:44:22.363 --> 00:44:23.397
Yeah?

715
00:44:23.731 --> 00:44:25.699
There was a dense fog
everywhere.

716
00:44:26.500 --> 00:44:29.504
And suddenly it was like
the whole fjord was sort of...

717
00:44:29.638 --> 00:44:30.871
boiling up.

718
00:44:31.606 --> 00:44:33.240
[hissing]

719
00:44:35.610 --> 00:44:37.912
Then a giant shadow appeared.

720
00:44:40.047 --> 00:44:41.949
And then it just vanished.

721
00:44:47.556 --> 00:44:50.024
-[muffled pop music]
-[rain falling softly]

722
00:44:58.299 --> 00:44:59.433
[engine rumbling]

723
00:44:59.568 --> 00:45:02.169
Let's stop here.
We don't need to go any closer.

724
00:45:03.771 --> 00:45:07.007
-Where is it?
-See that yellow buoy
with the light?

725
00:45:07.141 --> 00:45:09.376
-Right there.
-You have your diving gear?

726
00:45:09.743 --> 00:45:11.045
-Who. me?
-Yeah!

727
00:45:11.312 --> 00:45:13.113
[man]
No. I don't have my diving gear.

728
00:45:13.447 --> 00:45:16.016
-Are you kidding me?
-No. why should I have it?

729
00:45:16.150 --> 00:45:17.918
You wrote that in the chat.
you would bring your

730
00:45:18.052 --> 00:45:19.853
-gear.
-I... forgot.

731
00:45:20.287 --> 00:45:22.056
-[indistinct grunting dialogue]
-Could you just stop?

732
00:45:22.189 --> 00:45:24.091
[pop music continues]

733
00:45:29.631 --> 00:45:30.864
[siren wails]

734
00:45:31.065 --> 00:45:33.434
-Is she over there?
-Yes. the yellow one.

735
00:45:34.468 --> 00:45:35.869
[suspenseful music]

736
00:45:36.003 --> 00:45:37.338
[soft beeping]

737
00:45:50.985 --> 00:45:52.920
[flies buzzing]

738
00:45:54.955 --> 00:45:56.423
[sighs]

739
00:45:58.892 --> 00:46:00.361
[eerie sting]

740
00:46:02.463 --> 00:46:03.864
[grunts]

741
00:46:04.031 --> 00:46:05.933
Did anyone see what happened?

742
00:46:11.839 --> 00:46:13.841
[eerie sting]

743
00:46:20.715 --> 00:46:22.449
[music increases. then halts]

744
00:46:22.584 --> 00:46:23.784
[tape whirring]

745
00:46:24.218 --> 00:46:25.953
[interviewer] <i>Olav. can you tell</i>
<i>me how big it was?</i>

746
00:46:26.153 --> 00:46:29.823
<i>No. I don't wanna answer that.</i>
<i>because I'm not exactly sure.</i>

747
00:46:29.957 --> 00:46:31.325
<i>But it was at least 200 meters.</i>

748
00:46:31.458 --> 00:46:33.427
<i>give or take a few.</i>
<i>I'm sure of that.</i>

749
00:46:33.927 --> 00:46:36.063
-[interviewer]
<i>It was really that big?</i>
-[young Olav] <i>Yeah.</i>

750
00:46:36.397 --> 00:46:38.866
<i>And afterwards. some porpoises</i>
<i>came by over there.</i>

751
00:46:38.999 --> 00:46:42.303
<i>And they were jumping all over</i>
<i>and were completely spooked.</i>

752
00:46:42.671 --> 00:46:45.472
<i>I just didn't like it.</i>
<i>it made me feel weird.</i>

753
00:46:45.674 --> 00:46:46.974
[interviewer] <i>So you're saying</i>
<i>they were...</i>

754
00:46:47.107 --> 00:46:48.809
[man] I can't dive in this.

755
00:46:50.411 --> 00:46:51.812
-[young Olav] <i>Yeah.</i>
-[man] I seriously think

756
00:46:51.945 --> 00:46:52.980
there are mice in that suit.

757
00:46:53.113 --> 00:46:54.381
[Maria sighs]

758
00:46:54.582 --> 00:46:56.116
[young Olav continues
indistinctly on video]

759
00:46:56.250 --> 00:46:58.520
-[tape recorder clicks]
-It has happened before.

760
00:46:58.720 --> 00:47:01.155
Fish. scared on the land.

761
00:47:02.189 --> 00:47:03.857
-Hey!
-[Olav] Hi.

762
00:47:04.759 --> 00:47:06.026
Come with me.

763
00:47:06.695 --> 00:47:09.263
What are you doing?
Eastern boys. huh?

764
00:47:09.396 --> 00:47:12.032
Yeah. Cato and Hallvard.
this is Olav.

765
00:47:20.809 --> 00:47:22.076
[Olav sighs]

766
00:47:23.712 --> 00:47:25.145
What do you guys need?

767
00:47:25.780 --> 00:47:27.515
[engine revving]

768
00:47:29.116 --> 00:47:30.351
[somber music]

769
00:47:34.121 --> 00:47:36.023
[muffled high-pitched ring]

770
00:47:38.392 --> 00:47:40.194
[engine revving]

771
00:47:41.629 --> 00:47:43.030
[screaming]

772
00:47:50.471 --> 00:47:52.206
[muffled growl]

773
00:47:53.641 --> 00:47:55.376
[eerie sting]

774
00:47:55.844 --> 00:47:57.277
[wet skittering]

775
00:47:58.145 --> 00:48:00.347
[high-pitched ringing]

776
00:48:04.918 --> 00:48:06.153
[clicks]

777
00:48:12.226 --> 00:48:14.294
[computer voice]
<i>Above blocking level.</i>

778
00:48:14.662 --> 00:48:16.263
<i>Above blocking level.</i>

779
00:48:17.766 --> 00:48:19.400
<i>Above blocking--</i>

780
00:48:24.405 --> 00:48:25.874
It sounds normal to me.

781
00:48:26.006 --> 00:48:28.976
Yeah. except that it was
recorded 1300 meters from here.

782
00:48:38.553 --> 00:48:40.320
-No. That can't be right.
-[Johanne] Yes. Yes!

783
00:48:40.454 --> 00:48:42.990
The frequency goes all the way
to the bottom of the fjord.

784
00:48:45.359 --> 00:48:46.561
I made sure to set up
the blockers.

785
00:48:46.694 --> 00:48:48.228
Then the blockers
aren't working. Erik!

786
00:48:48.362 --> 00:48:49.798
-No. I know they're working.
-It's not safe.

787
00:48:49.930 --> 00:48:51.965
There's something wrong
with Sonic Lice. okay?

788
00:48:52.099 --> 00:48:53.434
The logs don't add up.

789
00:49:00.842 --> 00:49:03.545
We couldn't make it
safe either. right?

790
00:49:03.711 --> 00:49:05.279
Because it was never safe.

791
00:49:09.383 --> 00:49:10.819
[music intensifying]

792
00:49:10.951 --> 00:49:12.186
[sighs]

793
00:49:14.889 --> 00:49:16.123
-[Erik] Wake up!
-[Georg grunts]

794
00:49:16.256 --> 00:49:19.159
What?
Hey. what are you doing. man?

795
00:49:20.160 --> 00:49:21.529
I need the live log
to check something.

796
00:49:21.663 --> 00:49:23.565
-[Georg] Check what. Erik?
-[computer beeping]

797
00:49:23.765 --> 00:49:25.900
Help me.
I need to check the blockers.

798
00:49:26.033 --> 00:49:27.434
It's all fine.
But I'll let you know

799
00:49:27.569 --> 00:49:29.102
if there's anything abnormal.
okay?

800
00:49:29.236 --> 00:49:30.738
[cellphone buzzing]

801
00:49:32.740 --> 00:49:34.308
[Erik]
<i>Did you tell Georg to turn off</i>

802
00:49:34.441 --> 00:49:36.276
<i>the blockers on Sonic Lice?</i>

803
00:49:37.478 --> 00:49:39.547
<i>-How long has</i>
<i>this been going on?</i>
-[clears throat]

804
00:49:40.280 --> 00:49:42.216
<i>-Jostein?</i>
-Let's just calm down. okay?

805
00:49:42.349 --> 00:49:43.952
This could fuck up
the entire fjord.

806
00:49:44.084 --> 00:49:45.385
[Jostein] <i>Did Johanne say that?</i>

807
00:49:45.520 --> 00:49:46.788
<i>Johanne's just</i>
<i>trying to scare us.</i>

808
00:49:46.921 --> 00:49:48.155
<i>I need spotless salmon</i>

809
00:49:48.288 --> 00:49:49.958
<i>while the investors are here.</i>

810
00:49:51.626 --> 00:49:54.294
<i>It's just for a few days.</i>
<i>then we will adjust it back.</i>

811
00:49:54.428 --> 00:49:57.064
<i>We're signing now. You're about</i>
<i>to become very rich. Erik.</i>

812
00:49:57.197 --> 00:50:00.267
[scoffs] They'll shut all this
shit down. you know that. right?

813
00:50:00.935 --> 00:50:03.170
I'll come out there
as soon as I'm done here.

814
00:50:03.571 --> 00:50:06.774
Alright? B-- But now I have
to go. so I'm hanging up.

815
00:50:06.908 --> 00:50:08.141
[phone beeps]

816
00:50:14.481 --> 00:50:15.650
[thuds]

817
00:50:16.049 --> 00:50:17.384
[dramatic music]

818
00:50:20.187 --> 00:50:21.421
[Jostein] Sorry about that.

819
00:50:21.556 --> 00:50:24.458
My wife. uh...
she's a police officer.

820
00:50:24.592 --> 00:50:26.694
[woman] Everything looks great.
Jostein.

821
00:50:26.828 --> 00:50:29.697
We would love to join you on
this journey.

822
00:50:30.464 --> 00:50:32.366
[chuckles] Amazing.

823
00:50:33.100 --> 00:50:35.168
[chuckles] Amazing.

824
00:50:35.937 --> 00:50:37.437
[sighs] Champagne?

825
00:50:38.506 --> 00:50:40.340
It's a very special Grand Cru

826
00:50:40.474 --> 00:50:43.310
that I've saved for a very
special occasion.

827
00:50:43.611 --> 00:50:44.846
[gasp]

828
00:50:45.045 --> 00:50:47.180
-[glass shatters]
-[screaming]

829
00:50:50.083 --> 00:50:52.319
[women screaming]

830
00:50:55.723 --> 00:50:57.792
[typing]

831
00:51:03.463 --> 00:51:05.399
[computer beeping]

832
00:51:08.870 --> 00:51:10.337
[computer chimes]

833
00:51:12.272 --> 00:51:14.474
[suspenseful music]

834
00:51:17.912 --> 00:51:19.313
[Johanne] Look at this!

835
00:51:20.715 --> 00:51:22.416
[computer beeping]

836
00:51:27.120 --> 00:51:28.990
It's not just the salmon
you've deloused.

837
00:51:29.557 --> 00:51:33.393
If what we found was a parasite.
do you know what that entails?

838
00:51:37.732 --> 00:51:40.500
Either you haven't calibrated
that equipment of yours...

839
00:51:41.501 --> 00:51:43.370
...or it's a monster salmon.

840
00:51:43.805 --> 00:51:44.906
[Johanne] Erik...

841
00:51:46.173 --> 00:51:48.408
-We're turning off
Sonic Lice. Georg.
-[Johanne] Yeah.

842
00:51:48.543 --> 00:51:51.512
No. Not until Jostein's here.

843
00:51:52.145 --> 00:51:53.681
[music increases]

844
00:51:58.720 --> 00:52:00.054
[engine revving]

845
00:52:01.188 --> 00:52:03.290
Could you please pack up?
We're closing the beach down.

846
00:52:03.423 --> 00:52:05.392
[man] Okay. guys. out of the
water. come on now.

847
00:52:05.526 --> 00:52:07.327
[Henriette] Could you please get
the kids out of the water?

848
00:52:08.029 --> 00:52:11.733
-Okay. guys. listen.
the boat will be here very soon.
-[indistinct arguing]

849
00:52:11.899 --> 00:52:15.103
We will all be waiting maybe
ten or 15 minutes more.

850
00:52:15.235 --> 00:52:17.605
and. uh. all will be okay. Okay?

851
00:52:17.739 --> 00:52:20.041
Hey. what's up?
Are you missing a boat?

852
00:52:20.440 --> 00:52:22.142
[sighs] It should've
been here ages ago.

853
00:52:22.275 --> 00:52:25.013
-Yeah? How long?
-Far too long.

854
00:52:25.245 --> 00:52:27.615
[Cato] Where's that hood?
There it is.

855
00:52:28.516 --> 00:52:30.018
[Hallvard] Cato. you ready?

856
00:52:30.250 --> 00:52:31.786
[groans and sighs]

857
00:52:32.419 --> 00:52:33.621
-[Cato] Careful. okay?
-[Maria] You guys.

858
00:52:33.755 --> 00:52:34.889
-shut up!
-[Hallvard] I'm being careful.

859
00:52:35.623 --> 00:52:37.692
[rushing footsteps approaching]

860
00:52:39.594 --> 00:52:40.728
What's going on here?

861
00:52:40.862 --> 00:52:42.462
She wants
to turn off Sonic Lice.

862
00:52:43.031 --> 00:52:44.632
Uh. she doesn't have
the power to do that.

863
00:52:44.766 --> 00:52:46.466
Just please listen to me.
Jostein. okay?

864
00:52:46.601 --> 00:52:48.168
It's not just affecting
the salmon.

865
00:52:48.301 --> 00:52:50.071
This is affecting
the entire fjord.

866
00:52:50.203 --> 00:52:51.506
All the way to the bottom.

867
00:52:51.639 --> 00:52:53.074
Are you lecturing me about the
Sognefjord?

868
00:52:53.206 --> 00:52:54.274
Jostein...

869
00:52:54.642 --> 00:52:56.243
-[eerie music]
-[sighs]

870
00:52:56.376 --> 00:52:58.378
We have to turn it off. okay?

871
00:53:02.083 --> 00:53:03.618
Then contact Food Safety!

872
00:53:04.217 --> 00:53:05.887
We're not turning anything off.

873
00:53:06.087 --> 00:53:07.320
[drops vest]

874
00:53:14.494 --> 00:53:16.296
Georg. sit down.

875
00:53:19.167 --> 00:53:20.935
[Maria] Okay. please be careful.

876
00:53:24.271 --> 00:53:26.373
[suspenseful music]

877
00:53:38.218 --> 00:53:41.221
[water bubbling]

878
00:53:47.260 --> 00:53:49.329
[water movement at distance]

879
00:53:53.835 --> 00:53:55.570
[eerie sting]

880
00:54:08.315 --> 00:54:09.684
[thud]

881
00:54:16.758 --> 00:54:18.192
-[thud]
-[muffled grunting]

882
00:54:18.325 --> 00:54:19.560
[computer beeping]

883
00:54:22.496 --> 00:54:24.932
Um. module three is offline.

884
00:54:25.066 --> 00:54:26.768
[keyboard clacking]

885
00:54:28.301 --> 00:54:30.938
-[heavy breathing]
-[Maria] Cato. did you do it?

886
00:54:31.072 --> 00:54:33.574
-Yeah. help me up. guys.
-[Maria] Yeah.

887
00:54:33.908 --> 00:54:36.376
Fuck! There's something
down there. Help me up!

888
00:54:36.511 --> 00:54:38.079
-[Maria grunting]
-[Cato screams]

889
00:54:38.212 --> 00:54:41.015
-[Hallvard] Cato. don't--
Don't let go!
-[Cato screaming]

890
00:54:41.149 --> 00:54:44.484
-[Maria and Caro screaming]
-[Hallvard] Cato. what's
happening? Cato. no!

891
00:54:47.188 --> 00:54:49.857
-[Maria sobbing]
-Cato! Cato!

892
00:54:50.558 --> 00:54:53.127
Help! Help!

893
00:54:53.393 --> 00:54:55.428
[computer beeping]

894
00:54:57.865 --> 00:55:00.001
There's someone
at the outermost pens.

895
00:55:06.941 --> 00:55:08.743
Maria? Fuck!

896
00:55:09.243 --> 00:55:11.679
[tense music]

897
00:55:13.781 --> 00:55:16.050
-[computer beeping]
-[keyboard clacking]

898
00:55:16.651 --> 00:55:18.820
[deep rumbling]

899
00:55:18.953 --> 00:55:21.388
[alarm wailing]

900
00:55:22.557 --> 00:55:23.991
Georg. turn it off.

901
00:55:24.792 --> 00:55:27.528
They're serial-connected.
It's not possible!

902
00:55:27.662 --> 00:55:29.730
I can't connect to any of them!

903
00:55:30.064 --> 00:55:31.599
[tense music continues]

904
00:55:31.799 --> 00:55:33.568
[Maria sobbing] Daddy!

905
00:55:35.069 --> 00:55:36.938
-What are you doing. sweetheart?
-[Maria cries]

906
00:55:37.071 --> 00:55:39.574
-[Jostein] Huh?
-He just disappeared. Daddy!

907
00:55:39.707 --> 00:55:41.374
We have to go down there.

908
00:55:41.843 --> 00:55:43.978
-We have to go down. please!
-[coughing]

909
00:55:44.111 --> 00:55:45.445
[retching]

910
00:55:45.947 --> 00:55:47.414
-Are you okay?
-[heavy thud]

911
00:55:47.582 --> 00:55:49.517
[Hallvard screams]

912
00:55:52.220 --> 00:55:55.089
-Get them inside!
-[Erik] Let's go. guys.
Come on. inside!

913
00:55:55.488 --> 00:55:56.958
You too. Johanne! Let's go.

914
00:55:58.292 --> 00:56:00.962
-Maria. come on!
Come on. let's go.
-Get inside! In. in!

915
00:56:02.063 --> 00:56:03.931
[water splashing]

916
00:56:05.465 --> 00:56:06.701
[sighs]

917
00:56:09.837 --> 00:56:11.806
-Jostein. you have to let go.
Go. go!
-Y-- Yeah. yeah.

918
00:56:15.509 --> 00:56:17.578
[music fades]

919
00:56:19.146 --> 00:56:21.515
[wind blowing]

920
00:56:22.415 --> 00:56:24.151
[distant growl]

921
00:56:27.655 --> 00:56:29.957
-[water splashes]
-[Johanne gasps]

922
00:56:30.658 --> 00:56:32.392
[distant growl]

923
00:56:33.194 --> 00:56:35.062
[muffled thuds and rumbling]

924
00:56:36.197 --> 00:56:37.965
[ominous music]

925
00:56:38.232 --> 00:56:40.467
[alarm wailing]

926
00:56:41.501 --> 00:56:42.970
[computer voice] <i>Anchor alarm.</i>

927
00:56:47.141 --> 00:56:49.810
<i>-Anchor alarm.</i>
-Oh. what the fuck.

928
00:57:03.758 --> 00:57:05.860
[music continues]

929
00:57:11.098 --> 00:57:13.034
[deep distant growl]

930
00:57:16.737 --> 00:57:18.906
[music increasing]

931
00:57:23.611 --> 00:57:25.146
[creature growling]

932
00:57:26.013 --> 00:57:27.848
[panting]

933
00:57:31.385 --> 00:57:33.187
[creature huffs]

934
00:57:37.291 --> 00:57:39.794
[deep breaths]

935
00:57:40.895 --> 00:57:42.863
[Johanne breathing shakily]

936
00:57:45.299 --> 00:57:47.001
[creature huffs]

937
00:57:47.635 --> 00:57:49.904
[wet. squishing movement]

938
00:58:02.283 --> 00:58:04.885
[uneasy music]

939
00:58:06.354 --> 00:58:08.556
[panting]

940
00:58:13.327 --> 00:58:15.262
[computer beeping]

941
00:58:25.940 --> 00:58:28.075
You guys. it's enormous.
[panting]

942
00:58:28.576 --> 00:58:30.044
[Jostein]
What the fuck was that?

943
00:58:30.344 --> 00:58:32.613
[Johanne]
We have to be completely quiet.

944
00:58:33.981 --> 00:58:35.549
-[metallic thud]
-[gasps]

945
00:58:38.352 --> 00:58:40.121
[floor creaking]

946
00:58:46.660 --> 00:58:48.262
[faint growling]

947
00:58:49.830 --> 00:58:51.632
[Maria] Johanne. what is it?

948
00:58:52.733 --> 00:58:54.135
[Johanne] Parasites.

949
00:58:58.172 --> 00:59:00.141
[faint growling]

950
00:59:06.515 --> 00:59:08.249
-[thud]
-[both gasp]

951
00:59:08.517 --> 00:59:10.651
[high-pitched chirring]

952
00:59:12.753 --> 00:59:14.722
[frantic skittering on glass]

953
00:59:16.624 --> 00:59:18.893
Come on. Maria. let's go.

954
00:59:22.263 --> 00:59:23.831
[thuds]

955
00:59:32.006 --> 00:59:33.508
[soft frantic thuds]

956
00:59:33.641 --> 00:59:35.576
[shushing]

957
00:59:37.578 --> 00:59:39.747
[frantic skittering]

958
00:59:40.281 --> 00:59:42.283
[breathing shakily]

959
00:59:45.453 --> 00:59:47.154
[heavy metallic thud]

960
00:59:50.891 --> 00:59:53.427
[frantic skittering]

961
00:59:54.028 --> 00:59:55.696
[Jostein]
Maria. stay close to me.

962
00:59:58.567 --> 00:59:59.967
[gasp]

963
01:00:05.339 --> 01:00:06.774
[deep rumble]

964
01:00:10.512 --> 01:00:12.379
[alarm wailing]

965
01:00:12.947 --> 01:00:14.248
[Georg] What the fuck?

966
01:00:14.381 --> 01:00:15.783
[keyboard clacking]

967
01:00:15.916 --> 01:00:18.185
The whole rig is moving.
That shouldn't be possible.

968
01:00:18.319 --> 01:00:19.753
There's just no way!

969
01:00:22.223 --> 01:00:24.725
-Maria. come here!
-Let go of her! Stop!

970
01:00:26.193 --> 01:00:27.928
[ominous rumble]

971
01:00:28.462 --> 01:00:30.364
[frantic skittering]

972
01:00:30.798 --> 01:00:32.199
[skittering stops abruptly]

973
01:00:33.834 --> 01:00:36.303
[music builds]

974
01:00:38.672 --> 01:00:40.207
-[all gasp]
-[thud]

975
01:00:42.743 --> 01:00:44.211
[panting]

976
01:00:44.678 --> 01:00:46.247
[door slams]

977
01:00:51.385 --> 01:00:53.087
[deep rumble]

978
01:00:56.490 --> 01:00:58.092
[cries]

979
01:00:58.325 --> 01:01:00.794
-[grunting while stomping]
-[wet squeaking]

980
01:01:02.564 --> 01:01:04.832
-[Jostein] Come here.
-Go. go.

981
01:01:05.232 --> 01:01:06.433
Go. go now.

982
01:01:13.642 --> 01:01:15.743
[heavy breathing]

983
01:01:16.645 --> 01:01:18.312
[loud crash]

984
01:01:18.445 --> 01:01:20.381
[alarm wailing]

985
01:01:20.881 --> 01:01:22.183
Fuck this!

986
01:01:22.683 --> 01:01:23.951
[rapid thuds]

987
01:01:31.458 --> 01:01:33.394
[tense music]

988
